parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to engine components, leading to costly repairs, and stalling can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways.
symptoms: Engine temperature gauge rises above normal
engine stalls or shuts off without warning
engine hesitation or loss of power
coolant leaks or low coolant levels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cylinder failure can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and can also cause the engine to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine misfires
engine hesitation or loss of power
oil leaks or low oil pressure
engine noise or knocking sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cam tensioner failure can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and can also cause the engine to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine noise or tapping sounds
engine hesitation or loss of power
oil leaks or low oil pressure
engine misfires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Restrictions in the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the engine hesitates or misfires
the fuel line breather tube is blocked
the fuel line is clogged
the vehicle has difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light sensor can cause the brake lights to stay on continuously, leading to confusion for other drivers and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The brake lights remain on even when the brake pedal is not pressed
the brake lights do not turn off after the brake pedal is released.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause poor visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: One or both headlights do not turn on
headlights are dim or flickering
headlights have a reduced beam pattern.
